The paper deals with a graph coloring problem and presents a heuristic algorithm for it. This problem is a classic topic in discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and is also relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) as it involves optimization. The algorithm uses dynamic programming techniques, which are commonly used in computer science (cs.DS) and computational complexity (cs.CC). The paper also includes experimental results, which could fall under machine learning (cs.LG) as it involves comparing the performance of different algorithms.
